WEBVTT

00:03.036 --> 00:06.665
That many of you here tonight
came home not to a hero's welcome

00:06.773 --> 00:09.901
but to the hostility of the American people

00:10.010 --> 00:13.002
is a shameful fact of history.

00:20.987 --> 00:25.924
One that l will never understand
or forgive.

00:29.929 --> 00:35.629
But it also underscores our sacred duty,
notjust today but forever,

00:36.503 --> 00:42.237
to honor those who served with honor,
and to remember those who fell.

00:43.043 --> 00:47.912
Men and women whose ultimate sacrifice
must never be forgotten.

00:52.685 --> 00:55.347
There is probably no audience

00:55.422 --> 01:00.792
that understands better
that our freedom is not free.

01:01.594 --> 01:05.792
All right, you're my eyes out there.
Talk to me. Positions report.

01:06.800 --> 01:10.827
- Sector three clear.
- No sign of him in four.

01:11.504 --> 01:13.495
Sector six, report.

01:15.975 --> 01:17.135
Mulder?

01:17.243 --> 01:20.440
- He's here. l feel him.
- Then where is he?

01:20.713 --> 01:24.342
Hold on. l think l have him in section four.

01:25.218 --> 01:27.277
Can you confirm that, Scully?

01:33.426 --> 01:35.519
Positive. He's heading towards you, three.

01:35.628 --> 01:39.257
Positions hold. Three and four,
do you have eye contact?

01:42.001 --> 01:45.027
l have him in three.
He's coming towards you, Scully.

01:47.240 --> 01:49.936
Don't take your eyes off him, Scully.

01:54.180 --> 01:55.511
Mulder, he saw me.

01:57.217 --> 02:00.380
- He's heading towards the sound booth.
- l'm cutting him off.

02:00.653 --> 02:02.985
Talk to me, people. Does anybody have him?

02:08.527 --> 02:10.689
What's happening, Scully?

02:12.699 --> 02:14.599
l'm closing on him.

02:14.767 --> 02:17.395
- Do you have him in three?
- Negative.

02:19.606 --> 02:21.597
Scully?

02:22.242 --> 02:25.973
- Scully.
- l lost him. You got him, three?

02:26.479 --> 02:28.777
l don't see him, Scully.

02:28.848 --> 02:30.839
What's happening?

02:31.084 --> 02:33.951
- l can't see him anywhere.
- He must be headed your way.

02:34.387 --> 02:36.855
- You got him, Mulder?
- Not yet.

02:39.926 --> 02:41.018
l got him.

02:46.733 --> 02:47.927
l lost him.

02:50.136 --> 02:52.502
Mulder, he's right in front of you.

02:53.506 --> 02:56.873
- He's got a gun.
- General, get off the stage.

03:01.681 --> 03:04.013
l can't see him. l can't see him.

